mbia: people and landscapes in transition |publisher=Univ. of British Columbia Press |year=2000 |isbn=0-7748-0784-9}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Muckle |first=Robert James |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8zBQ951iVncC&pg=PP1&dq=British%20Columbia#v=onepage |title=The First Nations of British Columbia: an anthropological survey |publisher=Univ. of British Columbia Press |year=1998 |isbn=0-7748-0663-X}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Thirkell |first=Fred |url=https://archive.org/details/britishcolumbia10000thir |title=British Columbia 100 years ago: portraits of a province |last2=Scullion |first2=Bob |publisher=Heritage House Pub |year=2002 |isbn=1-894384-49-0 |quote=British Columbia. |url-access=registration}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Ver Berkmoes |first=Ryan |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yfFTSXftIOcC&pg=PP1&dq=British%20Columbia#v=onepage |title=Guide to \"British Columbia\" |last2=Lee |first2=John |publisher=Lonely Planet |year=2007 |isbn=978-1-74104-584-0}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links|voy=British Columbia|collapsible=collapsed}}\n* [http://www.gov.bc.ca Government of British Columbia website]\n* [http://www.hellobc.com Tourism British Columbia official website]\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.gov.bc.ca/bcfacts/ |title=BC Facts |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130707193800/http://www.gov.bc.ca/bcfacts/ |archive-date=July 7, 2013 |access-date=July 10, 2013}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150624003733/http://www.newsroom.gov.bc.ca/ Newsroom]\n* [http://www.bcstats.gov.bc.ca/Home.aspx/ BCStats & Infoline Weekly Digest]\n* {{curlie|Regional/North_America/Canada/British_Columbia}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.bcarchives.gov.bc.ca/index.htm |title=Provincial Archives including online photo database |archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20021013074240/http%3A//www.bcarchives.gov.bc.ca/index.htm |archive-date=October 13, 2002 |access-date=May 15, 2019}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.vpl.vancouver.bc.ca/find/cat/C393/ |title=Vancouver Public Library; Historical Photographs of BC & the Yukon |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090324042144/http://www.vpl.vancouver.bc.ca/find/cat/C393/ |archive-date=March 24, 2009 |access-date=March 10, 2009}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.multiculturalcanada.ca/vpl |title=BC Multicultural Photographs from the Vancouver Public Library \u2013 searchable photo database |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121205230512/http://www.multiculturalcanada.ca/vpl |archive-date=December 5, 2012 |access-date=June 5, 2008}}\n* [http://maps.gov.bc.ca BC Government online map archive]\n\n{{Subdivisions of British Columbia}}\n{{Topics on British Columbia}}\n{{Provinces and territories of Canada}}\n{{Canada topics}}\n{{Coord|54|N|125|W|type:adm1st_scale:10000000_region:CA-BC|display=title}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:British Columbia| ]]\n[[Category:1871 establishments in Canada]]\n[[Category:Provinces of Canada]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1871]]\n[[Category:Pacific Northwest]]\n[[Category:Western Canada]]\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEconomy:Fixed cite error", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Columbia"}
{"title_page": "Sunday Mornin' (album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Sunday Mornin'\n| type       = Album\n| artist     = [[Grant Green]]\n| cover      = Sunday Mornin'.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = End of November 1962<ref>[https://books.google.it/books?id=OhgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA20&dq=Grant+Green+Sunday+4099&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0CCEQ6AEwAGoVChMInZvs29TRxwIVRqhyCh2iZQ5p#v=onepage&q=Grant%20Green%20Sunday%204099&f=false ''Billboard'' Dec 1, 1962]</ref>\n| recorded   = June 4, 1961<br><small>[[Van Gelder Studio]], [[Englewood Cliffs]]\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Jazz blues]]\n| length     = 47:04 <small>CD reissue\n| label      = [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]]<br><small>BST 84099\n| producer   = [[Alfred Lion]]\n| chronology = [[Grant Green]]\n| prev_title = [[Green Street (album)|Green Street]]\n| prev_year  = 1961\n| next_title = [[Grantstand]]\n| next_year  = 1961\n}}\n\n'''''Sunday Mornin'''''' is an album by the American jazz guitarist [[Grant Green]] released on the [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] label in 1961.<ref name=\"Green discography\">[http://www.jazzdisco.org/grant-green/catalog/#blue-note-blp-4099 Grant Green discography] accessed September 14, 2010</ref> The CD reissue adds one bonus track recorded at the same session.\n\n==Reception==\nThe [[Allmusic]] review by Steve Huey awarded the album 3 stars and stated \"Green is tasteful and elegant as always, and the results make for an enjoyable addition to his discography, even if there are more distinctive Green albums available\".<ref name=\"Allmusic\">Huey, S. [{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r154343|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic Review] accessed September 14, 2010</ref>\n\nThe ''[[All About Jazz]]'' review by Norman Weinstein stated that \"There's not a bad tune on this peerless set, and whatever your feelings about Green's place in jazz history, it's highly recommended\".<ref>Weinstein, N. [http://www.allaboutjazz.com/php/article.php?id=18437 Sunday Mornin' Review] ''All About Jazz'', August 5, 2005</ref>\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = ''[[Allmusic]]''\n| rev1Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"Allmusic\"/>\n| rev2 = ''[[Encyclopedia of Popular Music]]''\n| rev2Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite book|last=Larkin|first=Colin|authorlink=Colin Larkin|title=Encyclopedia of Popular Music|year=2007|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|edition=4th|isbn=978-0195313734|title-link=Encyclopedia of Popular Music}}</ref> \n}}\n\n==Track listing==\n:''All compositions by Grant Green except as indicated''\n\n# \"Freedom March\" \u2013 8:42\n# \"Sunday Mornin'\" \u2013 4:01\n# \"Exodus\" ([[Ernest Gold (composer)|Ernest Gold]]) \u2013 7:01\n# \"[[God Bless the Child (Billie Holiday song)|God Bless the Child]]\" ([[Arthur Herzog, Jr.]] [[Billie Holiday]]) \u2013 7:21\n# \"Come Sunrise\" \u2013 4:32\n# \"[[So What (composition)|So What]]\" ([[Miles Davis]]) \u2013 9:48\n# \"Tracin' Tracy\" \u2013 5:39 <small>Bonus track on CD reissue</small>\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Grant Green]] \u2013 guitar\n*[[Kenny Drew]] \u2013 piano\n*[[Ben Tucker]] \u2013 [[double bass|bass]]\n*[[Ben Dixon (musician)|Ben Dixon]] \u2013 [[drum kit|drums]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Grant Green}}\n\n[[Category:Grant Green albums]]\n[[Category:1962 albums]]\n[[Category:Blue Note Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Alfred Lion]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Van Gelder Studio]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Sunday Mornin'\n| type       = Album\n| artist     = [[Grant Green]]\n| cover      = Sunday Mornin'.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = End of November 1962<ref>[https://books.google.it/books?id=OhgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA20&dq=Grant+Green+Sunday+4099&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0CCEQ6AEwAGoVChMInZvs29TRxwIVRqhyCh2iZQ5p#v=onepage&q=Grant%20Green%20Sunday%204099&f=false ''Billboard'' Dec 1, 1962]</ref>\n| recorded   = June 4, 1961<br><small>[[Van Gelder Studio]], [[Englewood Cliffs]]\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Jazz blues]]\n| length     = 47:04 <small>CD reissue\n| label      = [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]]<br><small>BST 84099\n| producer   = [[Alfred Lion]]\n| chronology = [[Grant Green]]\n| prev_title = [[Green Street (album)|Green Street]]\n| prev_year  = 1961\n| next_title = [[Grantstand]]\n| next_year  = 1961\n}}\n\n'''''Sunday Mornin'''''' is an album by the American jazz guitarist [[Grant Green]] released on the [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] label in 1961.<ref name=\"Green discography\">[http://www.jazzdisco.org/grant-green/catalog/#blue-note-blp-4099 Grant Green discography] accessed September 14, 2010</ref> The CD reissue adds one bonus track recorded at the same session.\n\n==Reception==\nThe [[Allmusic]] review by Steve Huey awarded the album 3 stars and stated \"Green is tasteful and elegant as always, and the results make for an enjoyable addition to his discography, even if there are more distinctive Green albums available\".<ref name=\"Allmusic\">Huey, S. [{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r154343|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic Review] accessed September 14, 2010</ref>\n\nThe ''[[All About Jazz]]'' review by Norman Weinstein stated that \"There's not a bad tune on this peerless set, and whatever your feelings about Green's place in jazz history, it's highly recommended\".<ref>Weinstein, N. [http://www.allaboutjazz.com/php/article.php?id=18437 Sunday Mornin' Review] ''All About Jazz'', August 5, 2005</ref>\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = ''[[Allmusic]]''\n| rev1Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"Allmusic\"/> \n}}\n\n==Track listing==\n:''All compositions by Grant Green except as indicated''\n\n# \"Freedom March\" \u2013 8:42\n# \"Sunday Mornin'\" \u2013 4:01\n# \"Exodus\" ([[Ernest Gold (composer)|Ernest Gold]]) \u2013 7:01\n# \"[[God Bless the Child (Billie Holiday song)|God Bless the Child]]\" ([[Arthur Herzog, Jr.]] [[Billie Holiday]]) \u2013 7:21\n# \"Come Sunrise\" \u2013 4:32\n# \"[[So What (composition)|So What]]\" ([[Miles Davis]]) \u2013 9:48\n# \"Tracin' Tracy\" \u2013 5:39 <small>Bonus track on CD reissue</small>\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Grant Green]] \u2013 guitar\n*[[Kenny Drew]] \u2013 piano\n*[[Ben Tucker]] \u2013 [[double bass|bass]]\n*[[Ben Dixon (musician)|Ben Dixon]] \u2013 [[drum kit|drums]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Grant Green}}\n\n[[Category:Grant Green albums]]\n[[Category:1962 albums]]\n[[Category:Blue Note Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Alfred Lion]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Van Gelder Studio]]\n", "name_user": "Muso805", "label": "safe", "comment": "4 star rating from 10 volume 4th Edition Oxford University Press, EPM 2007", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunday_Mornin%27_(album)"}
{"title_page": "List of United States pay television channels", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Refimprove|date=September 2019}}\nThe following is a list of '''[[pay television]] [[television network|networks]] broadcasting or receivable in the United States''', organized by broadcast area and genre. \n\nSome television providers use one or more channel slots for east/west feeds, high definition services, secondary audio programming and access to [[video on demand]].\n\nNot all channels are available on all providers and some are also available on free-to-air stations.\n\nThis list may be incomplete and uses limited sources relative to the 2,675<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://broadbandnow.com/All-Providers|title=Live list of TV providers in the United States|last=|first=|date=28 January 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> TV providers in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.somervillema.gov/sites/default/files/somerville-ma-comcast-xfinity-cable-lineup.pdf|title=Comcast Xfinity Lineup|last=|first=|date=28 January 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.att.com/ecms/dam/att/consumer/support/landingpage/userguides/pdf/u-verse-channel-directory.pdf|title=AT&T U-verse Channel Lineup|last=|first=|date=28 January 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.verizon.com/about/sites/default/files/clu/8899-CVAA-CLU-Guide.pdf|title=Verizon Fios Lineup|last=|first=|date=28 January 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== National Channels ==\nThe following channels are available on pay TV systems across the United States.\n\n{| class=\"toccolours sortable\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; font-size:90%; text-align:center; width:50%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Key\n! style=\"width:40%;\" | Description\n|-\n| [[Television in the United States|Launch Date]] || The date the channel first started broadcasting, not necessarily the date its founding company was created.\n|-\n|[[Terrestrial television|OTA]]|| If Yes, this channel has affiliations with free-to-air terrestrial networks.\nSee also; [[List of United States over-the-air television networks|List of United States over-the-air television networks.]]\n|-\n|[[Timeshift channel|East/West]]|| If Yes, this channel offers time-shifted feeds of its network.\n|-\n|[[High-definition television|HD]]|| If Yes, this channel offers a High Definition feed.\nSee also; [[High-definition television in the United States]].\n|-\n|[[Video on demand|VOD]]|| If Yes this channel offers video on demand content to providers.\n|-\n|[[Secondary Audio Program|SAP]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://frontier.com/~/media/HelpCenter/Documents/tv/dish/dish-channel-guide.ashx?la=en|title=Dish Channel Guide.|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>|| If Yes, this channel offers secondary audio programming to providers, this usually contains either audio description or a Spanish language dub.\n|-\n| [[Nielsen ratings|Households]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/features/overcrowded-cable-sector-esquire-spike-fyi-1202012647/|title=Variety - PDF halfway down the page entitled Net Worth.|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>|| The total number of households with viewing access to the channel (Not including households where the channel is available but not subscribed to).\n|}\n\n=== English Language ===\n{| class=\"toccolours sortable\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; font-size:90%; text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Genre\n! style=\"width:12%;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:20%;\" | Owner (Subsidiary)\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Launch \nD